Title: Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind
Author: Yuval Noah Harari
My Review: Sapiens reads like a novel, but more real, more interesting, and in some ways, more terrifying than any novel. Harari walks through history from the dawn of humanity to our modern age and gives a thoughtful and thorough worldwide summary of the characteristics, revolutions, and events that have shaped our contemporary ways of seeing and interacting with the world. Along the way, he confronts, without necessarily trying to answer, many of the big questions our species faces. Fantastic read (or listen).

Title: Own the Day, Own Your Life: Optimised practices for waking, working, learning, eating, training, playing, sleeping and sex
Author: Aubrey Marcus
My Review:
Own the Day, Own your Life is a great read. It's funny and easy to understand, and offers hundreds of very specific actions and recipes that can contribute to making every day a great day. The way it presents some of the science seems faulty - sort of brosciency, but the citations are actually pretty solid. I especially like the format and attitude of each chapter - getting owned to owning it and then specific actions to "own it."

Good stuff!
